WEBVTT

00:06:58.371 --> 00:07:03.799
And I happen to know his brother,
who's also a brilliant director.

00:07:03.823 --> 00:07:05.545
And they have a same quality.

00:07:05.569 --> 00:07:07.810
When they talk about what they do,

00:07:07.834 --> 00:07:11.014
there is this brilliant
level of specificity.

00:07:11.038 --> 00:07:12.879
So they don't just say,

00:07:12.903 --> 00:07:17.405
"I really loved that film
by Alfred Hitchcock."

00:07:17.429 --> 00:07:19.683
Which is what 90 percent of us would say.

00:07:19.707 --> 00:07:21.588
What Zal would say is,

00:07:21.612 --> 00:07:25.355
"If you watched that film by Hitchcock,

00:07:25.379 --> 00:07:28.347
in the 30-second moment,
there is this scene where this happens

00:07:28.371 --> 00:07:30.705
and so-and-so says this,
and the camera does this,